# scripts/leak_audit.local — operator-private leak patterns
#
# Copy this file to `scripts/leak_audit.local` (which is gitignored) and add the
# patterns specific to YOUR deployment. leak_audit.py loads them and hard-fails
# on any match, in addition to the generic secret shapes it ships with.
#
# WHY THIS LIVES OUTSIDE THE COMMITTED SCRIPT: the list of things you are hiding
# is itself a map of what you are hiding. If you type your internal codenames or
# proprietary terms into the committed, world-readable leak_audit.py, that file
# becomes the very disclosure the audit exists to prevent. Keep them here.
#
# One Python regex per line. Blank lines and lines starting with '#' are ignored.
# Matching is case-insensitive.
#
# Put here (examples — REPLACE with your own; these are illustrative placeholders):
#   my-internal-codename
#   acme-strategy-v2
#   \bMYORG\b
#   private-host\.internal\.example
#   internal-metric-name          # a naming pattern specific to your project
#   0\.0177                       # a specific tuned constant
#   OldRotatedCredentialString    # a rotated-but-still-sensitive secret
